How to create infrastructure using terraform if want to create different resources like vm, storage, keyvalut, sqlDB, appservice, function app, azure traffice manager, with different subscriptions?

For an enterprise Azure environment (like Accenture, Microsoft, Deloitte, banking clients), you do not write everything in a single main.tf file. Instead, you follow a modular Terraform architecture that is reusable, scalable, and supports multiple Azure subscriptions.

Recommended Project Structure
terraform-azure-infra/
│
├── modules/
│   ├── resource-group/
│   ├── storage-account/
│   ├── virtual-machine/
│   ├── key-vault/
