Accenture Interview Question
Interviewer:

"Can you implement approvals in Terraform?"

Strong Answer:

"Terraform itself does not provide a manual approval feature. It focuses only on infrastructure provisioning. In enterprise environments, approvals are implemented in the CI/CD pipeline. In Azure DevOps, I would configure a multi-stage pipeline with a Plan stage that generates and publishes a Terraform plan, followed by an Apply stage that targets an Azure DevOps Environment. I would configure Approvals and Checks on that environment so designated approvers, such as a Team Lead, Change Advisory Board (CAB), or Operations Manager, must approve before the terraform apply step executes. This ensures infrastructure changes follow governance and change management policies."
